<bibRefCitation author="Rider, D. A. &amp; Schwertner, C. F. &amp; Vilimova, J. &amp; Redei, D. &amp; Kment, P. &amp; Thomas, D. B." box="[322,528,1420,1447]" pageId="5" pageNumber="480" pagination="25 - 201" refId="ref7513" refString="Rider, D. A., Schwertner, C. F., Vilimova, J., Redei, D., Kment, P. &amp; Thomas, D. B. (2018) Higher systematics of the Pentatomoidea. In: McPherson, J. E. (Ed.), Invasive stink bugs and related species (Pentatomoidea): biology, higher systematics, semiochemistry, and management. CRC Press, Boca Raton, pp. 25 - 201. https: // doi. org / 10.1201 / 9781315371221 - 2" type="book chapter" year="2018">
Rider 
<emphasis box="[391,440,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="480">et al</emphasis>
. (2018)
</bibRefCitation>
suggest 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1876" box="[626,719,1420,1446]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Theloris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[626,719,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="480">Theloris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may need to be transferred to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Atkinson" authorityYear="1888" box="[1100,1214,1420,1446]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cappaeini">Cappaeini</taxonomicName>
based on the length and the shape of the peritreme of the metasternal gland. A final decision about the placement of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1876" box="[1243,1336,1456,1482]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Theloris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1243,1336,1456,1482]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="480">Theloris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
awaits a phylogenetic analysis.
</paragraph>
